4.Use a while loop to iterate over the matrix until all elements have been filled.
5.Within the while loop, use four for loops to fill in the elements of the matrix in spiral order:
6.The first loop fills in the top row of the matrix from left to right.
7.The second loop fills in the right column of the matrix from top to bottom.
8.The third loop fills in the bottom row of the matrix from right to left.
